main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a round object, the size of a small jet aircraft, over Steilacoom, Washington, on 25 May 1956.
interesting points: The object was pure white in color and estimated to be at an altitude of 10,000 feet., The object remained stationary due west of the observer., The sighting lasted for 1 hour and 46 minutes., The observer used binoculars to view the object., The report suggests the sighting was likely caused by the planet Venus.
sighted object: one round object, size of a small jet aircraft, pure white in color
